**Code Explanation:**

The script performs the following steps to execute the regression modeling and sensitivity analysis: 1. Data Loading & "Not Sure" Identification: Loads the cleaned dataset from Step 2 and the raw dataset to accurately identify respondents who answered "Not sure" for current (QEA_2) and future (QEB_2) job security. 2. Organizational Support Comparison: Computes and prints the mean Organizational Support Index for the "Sure" vs. "Not sure" groups to assess if uncertainty is linked to poor organizational communication. 3. Predictor Preparation & Standardization: Imputes missing values for continuous predictors using the mean and standardizes them to yield standardized beta coefficients. Categorical variables (HIDDG, QDB) are one-hot encoded. QKD (Agentic AI) is treated as a binary moderator. 4. Feature Engineering: Constructs the interaction term between regular training (QKB_1_4) and employee involvement (QKB_1_11), quadratic terms for the Task Transformation Indices to test for U-shaped relationships, and interaction terms with QKD. 5. VIF Calculation: Computes the Variance Inflation Factor (VIF) for all predictors to check for multicollinearity, flagging any features with a VIF > 5. 6. Ordinal Logistic Regression: Fits an OrderedModel (using the logit distribution) for both Current and Future Job Security, excluding the "Not sure" segment. It reports standardized coefficients, standard errors, z-scores, 95% confidence intervals, and FDR-adjusted p-values. 7. Sensitivity Analysis: Fits a Logistic Regression model predicting the probability of being in the "Not sure" segment based on the same predictors. Fits a Multinomial Logistic Regression model where "Not sure" is included as a distinct category alongside the ordered job security levels, allowing for a direct comparison of coefficients.

**Modifications:**

Added the main guard, ensured all paths use the data/ directory, removed hardcoded absolute paths for output, and ensured all imports are relative to the codebase folder.

